  "privacyPolicyTitle": "NutriFitApp privacy policy",
  "privacyPolicyLastUpdated": "April 7, 2026",
  "privacyPolicySection1Title": "1. Data controller",
  "privacyPolicySection1Paragraph1": "The data controller for the personal data processed through the NutriFit application is the owner or operating entity of the NutriFitApp service.",
  "privacyPolicySection1Paragraph2": "Controller contact details:",
  "privacyPolicySection1Bullet1": "Name or business name: Patricia Carmona Fernández.",
  "privacyPolicySection1Bullet2": "Tax ID/VAT number: Provided upon request.",
  "privacyPolicySection1Bullet3": "Address: Provided upon request.",
  "privacyPolicySection1Bullet4": "Contact email: aprendeconpatrica[ — at — ]gmail[ — dot — ]com",
  "privacyPolicySection2Title": "2. Applicable regulations",
  "privacyPolicySection2Paragraph1": "This Privacy Policy has been drafted in accordance with the applicable personal data protection regulations, in particular:",
  "privacyPolicySection2Bullet1": "Regulation (EU) 2016/679 of the European Parliament and of the Council of 27 April 2016, the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR).",
  "privacyPolicySection2Bullet2": "Spanish Organic Law 3/2018 of 5 December on Personal Data Protection and guarantee of digital rights (LOPDGDD).",
  "privacyPolicySection2Bullet3": "Any other applicable Spanish and European regulations.",
  "privacyPolicySection3Title": "3. What NutriFitApp is",
  "privacyPolicySection3Paragraph1": "NutriFitApp is an application focused on nutrition, health, sports, habit tracking, and personal organization. It may include features such as a user profile, tasks, shopping list, recipes, tips, healthy substitutions, training, nutritional scanner, notifications, additives, supplements, weight control, and tracking tools between the user and the professional.",
  "privacyPolicySection4Title": "4. What personal data we process",
  "privacyPolicySection4Paragraph1": "Depending on how you use the app, NutriFitApp may process the following categories of data:",
  "privacyPolicySection4Bullet1": "Identification data: name, nickname or alias, email address, profile image, and other registration data.",
  "privacyPolicySection4Bullet2": "Access and authentication data: credentials, session identifiers, security verifications, and elements associated with secure access to the account.",
  "privacyPolicySection4Bullet3": "App usage data: interactions, preferences, saved settings, and actions performed within the application.",
  "privacyPolicySection4Bullet4": "Data provided by the user: tasks, notes, comments, feelings, manually entered content, and any other information voluntarily provided.",
  "privacyPolicySection4Bullet5": "Data related to nutrition, wellness, physical activity, or personal tracking that the user chooses to add to the application.",
  "privacyPolicySection4Bullet6": "Technical and device data: technical identifiers, app version, operating system, language settings, and the minimum data needed for operation, security, and diagnostics.",
  "privacyPolicySection4Bullet7": "Data derived from push notifications, if the user enables them.",
  "privacyPolicySection4Bullet8": "Camera or image data, if the user uses features such as profile image, scanner, content capture, or images in activities.",
  "privacyPolicySection4Bullet9": "Data linked to calendar features, if the user decides to use schedule integrations.",
  "privacyPolicySection4Bullet10": "Any other data necessary to properly provide the services offered in the app.",
  "privacyPolicySection4Paragraph2": "If, in certain cases, data related to health or personal wellness is processed, such processing will only take place to the extent necessary to provide the functionality requested by the user and in accordance with the applicable legal basis.",
  "privacyPolicySection5Title": "5. Purposes of processing",
  "privacyPolicySection5Bullet1": "Create and manage the user account.",
  "privacyPolicySection5Bullet2": "Allow sign-in and keep the session authenticated.",
  "privacyPolicySection5Bullet3": "Provide the main NutriFitApp features.",
  "privacyPolicySection5Bullet4": "Manage the user profile.",
  "privacyPolicySection5Bullet5": "Allow tracking of habits, tasks, training, nutrition, and related content.",
  "privacyPolicySection5Bullet6": "Facilitate interaction between the user and the professional when that functionality is enabled.",
  "privacyPolicySection5Bullet7": "Send notifications related to account activity or features used by the user.",
  "privacyPolicySection5Bullet8": "Improve the user experience, stability, security, and performance of the app.",
  "privacyPolicySection5Bullet9": "Handle requests, incidents, or inquiries submitted by the user.",
  "privacyPolicySection5Bullet10": "Comply with applicable legal obligations.",
  "privacyPolicySection5Bullet11": "Protect the controller's legitimate interests regarding security, fraud prevention, service integrity, and protection against unauthorized access.",
  "privacyPolicySection6Title": "6. Legal basis",
  "privacyPolicySection6Paragraph1": "The legal bases that legitimize processing may be, depending on the case:",
  "privacyPolicySection6Bullet1": "Performance of the contractual or pre-contractual relationship when the user registers for and uses NutriFitApp.",
  "privacyPolicySection6Bullet2": "The user's consent for those features that require it.",
  "privacyPolicySection6Bullet3": "Compliance with legal obligations.",
  "privacyPolicySection6Bullet4": "The controller's legitimate interest in ensuring the security, continuity, and proper functioning of the application.",
  "privacyPolicySection6Paragraph2": "When processing is based on consent, the user may withdraw it at any time, without affecting the lawfulness of processing carried out before its withdrawal.",
  "privacyPolicySection7Title": "7. Data retention",
  "privacyPolicySection7Paragraph1": "Personal data will be kept for as long as necessary to fulfill the purpose for which it was collected and, thereafter, for the periods legally required to address potential liabilities.",
  "privacyPolicySection7Paragraph2": "When the user requests deletion of the account, their data will be deleted or anonymized in accordance with the internal retention policy and any applicable legal obligations.",
  "privacyPolicySection8Title": "8. User-initiated data deletion",
  "privacyPolicySection8Paragraph1": "NutriFitApp allows the user to delete all of their data by deleting the account directly from the application at any time.",
  "privacyPolicySection8Paragraph2": "Steps within the app to completely delete the account and its data:",
  "privacyPolicySection8Step1": "Sign in to NutriFitApp with your user account.",
  "privacyPolicySection8Step2": "Open Edit Profile.",
  "privacyPolicySection8Step3": "Within that screen, locate the account deletion option (the “Delete all my data” button).",
  "privacyPolicySection8Step4": "Tap Delete all my data.",
  "privacyPolicySection8Step5": "Confirm the deletion process.",
  "privacyPolicySection8Paragraph3": "After confirmation, the application will execute the deletion process for the account and associated data according to the system's operation, and will sign the user out.",
  "privacyPolicySection8Paragraph4": "If, for any reason, the user cannot complete the process from the app, they may also request deletion by writing to the contact email indicated above.",
  "privacyPolicySection9Title": "9. Data recipients",
  "privacyPolicySection9Paragraph1": "Data will NEVER be sold or disclosed to third parties.",
  "privacyPolicySection9Paragraph2": "Only the following may have access to the data:",
  "privacyPolicySection9Bullet1": "Qualified technical personnel solely for technological processes necessary for app operation, hosting, notifications, technical support, or related services.",
  "privacyPolicySection9Bullet2": "Data processors contracted by the controller, under the corresponding contractual safeguards.",
  "privacyPolicySection9Bullet3": "Public administrations, judges, courts, or competent authorities when there is a legal obligation.",
  "privacyPolicySection9Paragraph3": "There are no international data transfers outside the European Economic Area.",
  "privacyPolicySection10Title": "10. Device permissions",
  "privacyPolicySection10Paragraph1": "NutriFitApp may request device permissions only when they are necessary for a specific feature. For example:",
  "privacyPolicySection10Bullet1": "Camera: to capture images or use scanning features.",
  "privacyPolicySection10Bullet2": "Gallery or files: to select images or documents, or to save PDF documents from the app.",
  "privacyPolicySection10Bullet3": "Notifications: for relevant alerts within the app.",
  "privacyPolicySection10Bullet4": "Calendar: if the user decides to export or add events.",
  "privacyPolicySection10Bullet5": "Other permissions strictly necessary for certain application tools.",
  "privacyPolicySection10Paragraph2": "The user may revoke these permissions at any time from the device settings, although some features may no longer be available.",
  "privacyPolicySection11Title": "11. Information security",
  "privacyPolicySection11Paragraph1": "NutriFitApp applies reasonable technical and organizational measures to protect personal data against loss, alteration, unauthorized access, disclosure, or destruction. Information is encrypted in transit.",
  "privacyPolicySection11Paragraph2": "However, the user should be aware that no Internet transmission or storage system can guarantee absolute security.",
  "privacyPolicySection12Title": "12. User rights",
  "privacyPolicySection12Paragraph1": "The user may exercise the following rights at any time:",
  "privacyPolicySection12Bullet1": "Access.",
  "privacyPolicySection12Bullet2": "Rectification.",
  "privacyPolicySection12Bullet3": "Erasure.",
  "privacyPolicySection12Bullet4": "Objection.",
  "privacyPolicySection12Bullet5": "Restriction of processing.",
  "privacyPolicySection12Bullet6": "Portability.",
  "privacyPolicySection12Bullet7": "Withdrawal of consent, when processing is based on it.",
  "privacyPolicySection12Paragraph2": "To exercise these rights, the user may:",
  "privacyPolicySection12Bullet8": "Use the functions available within the app, when they exist.",
  "privacyPolicySection12Bullet9": "Contact the controller through the contact email indicated above.",
  "privacyPolicySection12Paragraph3": "The request must allow the applicant to be reasonably identified.",
  "privacyPolicySection12Paragraph4": "The user also has the right to lodge a complaint with the Spanish Data Protection Agency (AEPD) if they believe their rights have not been properly addressed:",
  "privacyPolicySection12Paragraph5": "https://www.aepd.es/",
  "privacyPolicySection13Title": "13. Minors",
  "privacyPolicySection13Paragraph1": "NutriFitApp is not generally intended for minors without the intervention or authorization of their legal representatives when required. If we detect that personal data of a minor has been collected in breach of the applicable regulations, the appropriate measures will be taken for its deletion.",
  "privacyPolicySection14Title": "14. Accuracy and user responsibility",
  "privacyPolicySection14Paragraph1": "The user guarantees that the data provided is true, accurate, and up to date, and undertakes to communicate any changes.",
  "privacyPolicySection14Paragraph2": "The user shall be responsible for any damages or losses that may arise from providing false, inaccurate, or outdated data.",
  "privacyPolicySection15Title": "15. Changes to this policy",
  "privacyPolicySection15Paragraph1": "NutriFitApp may update this Privacy Policy to adapt it to legal, technical, or functional changes. When changes are relevant, the user will be informed through appropriate means.",
  "privacyPolicySection16Title": "16. Contact",
  "privacyPolicySection16Paragraph1": "For any matter related to privacy or data protection, you can contact:",
  "privacyPolicySection16Paragraph2": "aprendeconpatrica[ — at — ]gmail[ — dot — ]com",
